args: Huh? Was that a child crying?
It came from over there.\nC'mon, let's check it out!
Hey! What's the big idea making a\nbunch of kids cry like that, jerk?!
I meant no harm, madam, I assure you.\nI was merely reading them a picture book.
...Hey, wait. If you were reading them\na picture book, why were they crying?
＂However, no hero came to save the\nimperiled princess. Nay, not a one.＂
＂And with a terrible cry, she was gobbled\nup for dinner by a many-eyed fiend.\nThus was all right in the world once more.＂
Um...did I just read what I think I read?
No wonder the kids turned on the\nwaterworks!
Yes, well, perhaps that ending did need\na little work. If you allow me to read you\none of these other stories, I'm certain—
Okay, what's your damage?! Why are\nyou reading some weirdo story to a\nbunch of little kids?!
If that is how you already feel,\nI doubt my explanation will assuage\nyour concerns one way or the other.
I am Norwin, a picture-book artist.\nThe tale you just read is one of my works.
Wait. YOU wrote this?! That's...um...\nWell, this is rather awkward.
Oh, it's all right. I'm well aware that my\ntales tend to fall a bit outside the norm.
Okay, but if you know you're writing\nhorrible stories, why keep doing it?
Because I find myself unable\nto pen a happy ending.

Despite knowing even in my own mind
that such sad tales are not appreciated,
I somehow find myself unable to write
anything else.
So it's like writer's block, except...weird?

I thought perhaps the problem was in the
writing, and so attempted to tell my story
in oral form hoping a happy ending would
somehow force itself out. However...
Indeed. The tale was... Well, let us just\nsay I hope I have not permanently scarred\nany of the children.
Wow. You're a real piece of work.
I don't know if I've ever heard of\na problem quite like this before.
Hey, I've got an idea! The prince here\nloves to write stories, so why don't the\ntwo of you form a writing group?!
Notte, I just write silly stories as a hobby.\nNorwin is a professional.
Hold a moment. You are a prince?\nNot Prince {player_name}?!
Can it really be you? The seventh scion\nof the royal Alberian family?!
That's me all right. Er, have we met?

The rumors of your deeds are legion!
You help the weak fend off powerful foes,
and your heart is filled with bravery and
love for all of your fellows!
Yeah, he's a big-shot all right.\nNow make with the bowing!
However, I fear I've also heard an equally\nabundant number of...not-so-pleasant\ntales about you.
Ah, those stories are hogwash.\nHogwash, I tells ya!

Yes, that seems all but certain now. For if
there's one thing I've learned in my line of
work, it is how to tell the cold truth of fact
from the fancy of fiction.
Okay, I think we can move on now...
And on that note, I've a request for you,\nYour Highness: You must allow me to\nplay a part in your tale!
You're a character right out of a story.\nIf I spend time with you, I might be able\nto finally find my elusive happy ending!
I beg this of you, let me join your ranks!\nI shall do anything!
I don't think I'm as impressive as all that,\nbut new friends are always welcome.
Thank you so much, Your Highness!\nI await your first command!
Well, how about you start by not calling\nme ＂Your Highness.＂ From now on,\nwe're friends of equal standing.
Oh! I, um... Yes, of course.
(It's just as the rumors said—he really IS\na prince from a children's faerie tale!)
